      <h1 class='title'>Public transport accessibility</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 19 July 2004 vol 424 c8WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_8ws' title='Col. 8WS &mdash; HC Deb 19 July 2004 vol 424 c8WS' name='column_8ws' href='#column_8ws' rel='bookmark'>8WS</a>
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040719_CWS_14' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The panel considers that draft revised RPG includes a sophisticated and innovative public transport accessibility policy which should help achieve spatial planning and transport objectives in an integrated way. The proposed changes clarify how the policy will be implemented.
      </p>
